dct_description_sm: Northwestern part of California shown on second Sanson model, with Bestrou Anien to north and Terre de Iesso to northwest, and Tartarie Partie de Asie and Iapon to far west. Extends between 180 and 240 deg. longitude.
First issued as inset on Louis Hennepin's map of 1697 (Entry 124) with left margin extending to longitude 175 and additional place name of Matzumay on Iapon.

Issued in his: Kort Beskrifning Om PROVINCIEN Nya Swerige uti AMERICA, som nu fortjden af the Engelske kallas PENSYLVANIA. Af larde och trowardige mans skrifter och berattelser ihopaletad och sammanskrefwen, samt med ath skillige figurer utzirad af THOMAS CAMPANIUS HOLM . -- Stockholm : Tryckt uti Kongl. boktr. hos S. Wankijfs ankia, med egen bekostnad, af J.H. Werner, 1702. Text in Swedish.
